, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASYz1qkoC.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitchy.com/justmindy/2026/03/24/barack-obama-obama-care-first-step-n2426368", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Obama Confesses Obamacare Was Only Step One Toward Destroying American Healthcare & 100% Socialized Medicine.", "last_comment_created": 1774356575384, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 5, "score_up": 33, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Obama admits Obamacare was only the first step toward socialized medicine and harming US healthcare.", "large_image": "bQNwQ3uyev0HJgT1.png", "title": "The Mask Comes Off: Obama Confesses Obamacare Was Only Step One Toward Destroying American Healthcare"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASYz1ql8x", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 28, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8509957, "raw_content": "The claim \u201cnone of our oil or resources come from Iran\u201d misses how oil pricing works. The U.S. may import little or no Iranian oil directly, but oil is still priced in a global market, and disruptions involving Iran can raise prices worldwide because they threaten major regional supply and shipping flows. EIA says about 20 million barrels per day, roughly 20% of global petroleum liquids consumption, moved through the Strait of Hormuz in 2024.\n\nFuel prices may come down if traders stop pricing in major supply risk, but it is wrong to pretend Iran does not matter just because the U.S. does not directly import Iranian oil. Iran matters because it can disrupt a globally important oil transit route and broader Gulf energy supply. If countries who do normally buy Iranian oil or oil from any of the surrounding areas that have been damaged and they can't get it, then they bid on the oil from elsewhere to meet their needs.", "author": "Hallelujah_Jesus", "created": 1774355669950, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Hallelujah_Jesus", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Why are gas prices so high?  Here's what an expert on bobistheoilguy has to say, \"The claim \u201cnone of our oil or resources come from Iran\u201d misses how oil pricing works. The U.S. may import little or no Iranian oil directly, but oil is still priced in a global market...", "last_comment_created": 1774367434180, "content": "<p>The claim \u201cnone of our oil or resources come from Iran\u201d misses how oil pricing works. The U.S. may import little or no Iranian oil directly, but oil is still priced in a global market, and disruptions involving Iran can raise prices worldwide because they threaten major regional supply and shipping flows. EIA says about 20 million barrels per day, roughly 20% of global petroleum liquids consumption, moved through the Strait of Hormuz in 2024.</p>\n<p>Fuel prices may come down if traders stop pricing in major supply risk, but it is wrong to pretend Iran does not matter just because the U.S. does not directly import Iranian oil. Iran matters because it can disrupt a globally important oil transit route and broader Gulf energy supply. If countries who do normally buy Iranian oil or oil from any of the surrounding areas that have been damaged and they can't get it, then they bid on the oil from elsewhere to meet their needs.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_